description: British citizen, Thomas Craig Sheldon, detained for assaulting cops in Puri's Lord Jagannath temple. Shrine off-limits for non-Hindus. Involved in scuffle, injuries sustained. Incident follows Poland woman's detention; previously caused nuisance near Sea Beach police station.

description: Foreign students attacked during Tarawih at Gujarat University, led by a hafiz during Ramzan. Prayer changed to congregational under Caliph Umar. Injuries to two students.

description: The decision to hand over Katchatheevu to Sri Lanka by Indira Gandhi in 1974 is a focal point in Tamil Nadu's Lok Sabha campaign. Sri Lanka's persistent pursuit, historical documents, and legal complexities highlight India's relinquishment of the island, sparking debates on sovereignty and geopolitical dynamics.

description: The Congress party is grappling with a substantial income tax demand of Rs 3,567 crore, creating hurdles for its political activities in the upcoming elections. Recent notices totaling over Rs 1,744 crore for fiscal years 2014-17 surpass the party's disclosed assets. Legal battles and fairness concerns surround the escalating tax demands.

description: Vijender Singh, a Jat, may contest Mathura against Hema Malini. His candidacy threatens Hema's 'Jat Bahu' status. Dharmendra's potential campaign could impact the election dynamics. Jats' support might sway the outcome in Mathura.
title: Vijender to enter Mathura ring versus Hema?

description: Archana Patil Chakurkar joined BJP in Mumbai after women's reservation bill. Fadnavis inducted her following Basavraj Patil's exit, aiming for Lingayat votes in Latur. Archana highlighted Nari Shakti Vandan Adhiniyam and welcomed Rajeshwar Niture from Udgir council.

description: Arunachal Pradesh CM Pema Khandu and 10 BJP candidates secure victory unopposed for upcoming assembly elections, reflecting BJP's popularity and satisfactory performance. Lok Sabha polls coincide on April 19. Counting on June 2 for assembly and June 4 for Lok Sabha. Previous elections saw BJP's significant wins. Notable unopposed victories in various constituencies.

description: PM Modi and Yogi Adityanath will address a rally in Meerut, marking a decade since BJP's victory over RLD. The event will feature Jayant Chaudhary, with strategic focus on Jats and Gurjars, and actor Arun Govil contesting the elections.

description: Congress to contest Ladakh in 2024, 3rd J&K seat. National Conference agrees. Congress sacrifices Anantnag for opposition unity. Senior leader confirms candidacy, despite NC's resistance.

title: Kerala ex-mantri's list of assets has no house, land or gold

Home Minister Amit Shah commended the government's commitment to farmers and marginalized communities through these awards. Modi recognized Karpoori Thakur for promoting social justice and M S Swaminathan for his pioneering work in agriculture. The awards highlight the leaders' legacies and inspire future generations.

description: Russian ambassador Alipov appreciates India's solidarity in condemning terrorism, highlighting joint efforts in combating terrorism and recent developments in suspects' arrests related to the Moscow attack.

Koli granted six weeks to surrender, emphasizing 'The law is harsh, but it is the law.' Koli stabbed wife, Savitaben, over money demand and legal intervention, mandated imprisonment.

description: RBI deputy governor M Rajeshwar Rao highlights the evolving financial landscape, challenges with new trends, and the importance of balanced regulations for niche players, emphasizing the need for responsible innovation in the market.

description: Central Board of Indirect Taxes and Customs implements measures to streamline GST operations, reduce unnecessary summons, and standardize procedures, aiming for quicker conclusions and improved taxpayer experience.

description: President Droupadi Murmu confers Bharat Ratna on former PMs P V Narasimha Rao and Chaudhary Charan Singh, M S Swaminathan, and Karpoori Thakur posthumously. PM Modi to honor L K Advani at his residence. Family members accept awards. Rao and Singh introduced economic reforms, Swaminathan boosted food self-sufficiency, Thakur served as Bihar CM.

description: Union finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman expects the March quarter's GDP growth to surpass 8%, building on the strong 8.4% growth in the Oct-Dec quarter. She emphasized the role of consumption in driving economic growth and clarified the recent income tax notices as part of digitization efforts. The official GDP data will be revealed on May 31.
title: Q4 growth set to push FY24 GDP up by 8% or more: Sitharaman

description: Central Adoption Resource Authority (Cara) introduces a new process to include children from child care institutions as 'no visitation' and 'unfit guardian' categories for adoption. States and UTs to expedite registrations under Supreme Court directives. Over 9,000 children identified in new categories, with 11,546 in 'orphan, abandoned, and surrendered' category. Data submission deadline to Ministry is April 8.

description: Peruvian authorities raided President Dina Boluarte's residence over alleged illicit enrichment, triggered by her display of luxury watches. The search, involving National Police and prosecutors, lasted five hours and extended to the government palace. Prime Minister criticized the move as 'disproportionate and unconstitutional,' sparking public outcry. Allegations raise concerns amid low approval ratings.

description: Lucknow (199 for 8) beat Punjab (178 for 5) by 21 runs to register their first win of IPL 2024. Punjab were very much in the chase until debutant rookie pacer Mayank was brought into the attack and rattled the batsmen with his express pace and bounce. He finished with figures of 3 for 27 in four overs, assisted by fellow uncapped pacer Mohsin Khan (2 for 34).

description: Following his cameo appearance against IPL 2023 runners-up Gujarat Titans, young batsman Sameer Rizvi of Chennai Super Kings attributed his brief yet impactful performance in his debut IPL match to Mahendra Singh Dhoni. The complex salvage operation involves floating cranes, tugboats, and divers facing challenges in visibility. Authorities are investigating the accident's cause and planning reconstruction efforts with federal aid.

description: Sunetra Pawar, Ajit Pawar's wife, is set to contest Baramati Lok Sabha seat against Supriya Sule.  The development sets the stage for a unique electoral face-off as Sunetra will be contesting against her sister-in-law and Sharad Pawar's daughter, Supriya Sule, in the Pawar family stronghold. "Voters have taken the fight in their hands," she said when asked about facing off with Supriya Sule.

The incident was first reported by Mikhail Razvozhayev, the Moscow-appointed leader in Sevastopol, who noted that a Russian warplane "crashed" off the Crimean coast. The Crimean Wind Telegram channel suggested that the aircraft was accidentally shot down following its departure from the Belbek military airfield.

Following Pooran's triumph in the toss and his decision to opt for batting first against Punjab Kings, the interim captain provided clarification regarding KL Rahul's absence from leading the side against Punjab Kings.

description: China has released a travel advisory for its citizens planning trips to the United States, cautioning them to brace for potential unexpected situations, including searches. Travelers have experienced thorough searches of their electronic devices and luggage, with some individuals being denied entry into the US. In response to these incidents, China's foreign ministry, along with its embassy and consulates in the US, have made formal complaints to American officials.

description: Indian Navy on Saturday said that 9 pirates who surrendered following the Navy's rescue operation on an Iranian fishing vessel are being brought to India for further legal action under the Maritime Anti-Piracy Act, 2022. The Navy on Friday had intercepted and successfully rescued the hijacked Iranian fishing vessel Al-Kambar 786 along with its 23-member Pakistani crew.

The five-time IPL-winning captain Rohit was replaced by Hardik Pandya ahead of the season, a move which did not go well with his fans. But Sidhu expressed that playing under Hardik's leadership will not diminish Rohit's stature.

description: Congress claimed that it has been served multiple income tax notices. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium in Visakhapatnam. CSK currently occupy the top spot on the points table. Meanwhile, Delhi Capitals are keen to secure their first win of the season.

Why was the new Telecom Bill passed when 143 opposition MPs were suspended? Is there any connection in this?" she asked. "Why was the rule of bidding removed in the allocation of internet spectrum from satellite through the new Telecom Bill?"
